    "recap_headline": "Lehigh University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BETHLEHEM, Pa.\u00a0\u2013 Lehigh baseball wrapped up its weekend series against the Holy Cross Crusaders on Sunday afternoon from J. David Walker Field. The Mountain Hawks fell 7-2 to secure a weekend sweep for the Crusaders.\nStarting pitcher Derek Volz earned the win for Holy Cross (9-13, 5-1 PL) after striking out four batters while allowing four hits and one earned run in 5.0 innings. Lehigh (5-15, 2-4 PL) reliever\nBrandon Coughlin\nwas credited with the loss after conceding the lead in the bottom of the fifth.\nThe Crusaders took an early 1-0 lead in the top of the first on a Van Coughlin RBI double. Lehigh starter\nJake Mulvehill\nthen settled in, allowing no runs through the next three innings. A\nRaffaele Rogers\nRBI single tied the game in the third inning and kept the score 1-1 headed to the fifth.\nGianni Royer broke the tie for Holy Cross in the top of the fifth courtesy of a sac-fly. Royer extended the Crusader lead to three in the top of the seventh on a two-RBI homer before\nTrystan Crawford\nresponded with a solo shot of his own to make it 4-2 headed to the eighth.\nThe Crusaders added three runs in the top of the eighth on a bases loaded walk and Braden Connors two-RBI single that gave Holy Cross a five-run advantage. Reliever Henry Harding recorded the outs necessary in the eighth and ninth innings to secure the weekend sweep for the Crusaders.\nRogers and Crawford both went 2-4 on the day while\nDom Patrizi\n,\nAidan Quinn\n,\nRyan Cochran\n,\nOwen Walewander\n,\nIan Wirtz\n, and\nSilvio Giardina\nalso recorded hits for Lehigh.\nMax Treonze\n,\nDavid Andolina\n,\nCole Kochanowicz\n, and\nRalph Gariano\nappeared on the mound for the Mountain Hawks in addition to Mulvehill and Coughlin.\nThe Mountain Hawks return to J. David Walker Field on Wednesday, March 25 at 3 p.m. to take on the FDU Knights.\nLike Lehigh Baseball on\nFacebook\n, follow on\nX\n(formerly Twitter)\u00a0and\nInstagram\nfor exclusive content, team updates and more.",
